text:
["The Nigerian Bar Association on Friday threatened President Muhammadu Buhari with legal action should he continue with what it described as “constitutional dereliction” in governance.","The NBA President, Abubakar Mahmoud, who gave the warning in his address at the opening of the association’s two-day National Executive Committee meeting in Kano on Thursday, accused the President of neglecting to act on the recommendations of the National Judicial Council to appoint 13 justices of the Court of Appeal since November 2017.","He said, “Similarly, several recommendations for appointments to the Bench of the Federal High Court and other federal courts are still pending, many months after these recommendations to the President.","“Acting on the recommendations of the NJC is not a matter of presidential discretion to be exercised whenever the President deems fit. It is a constitutional duty.","“Whilst the President is not bound to accept the recommendations, failure to act is a breach of the constitution. I, therefore, call on the President to act without further delay. This failure to act is causing unnecessary delays and avoidable negative consequences for the administration of justice across the country,” Mahmoud said.","The Publicity Secretary of the Kano State branch of the NBA, Yusuf Abdulsalam, described the event as a “quarterly constitutional requirement” of the association.","Copyright PUNCH.
